{
  "stem": "12462.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We hadn't figured out how that was going to work until the tribunal confronted the prosecution with the point that, look, you got to slow this trial down to be sure the defense and their attorneys can keep up with it immediately.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So this led to a tremendous amount of additional translating and paperwork.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Peter Eberhaal flew to England and with the tremendous priority attached to his work managed to recruit a large-- a larger number of translators and interpreters.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was an expert linguist himself in three languages-- German, French, and English-- and he did a magnificent job.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, then at that time, Lieutenant Eberhaal was-- he was born and raised in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when Hitler came to power, he chose to leave immediately and somehow got to the United States and worked his way up until he was first a-- a lieutenant, and he later went on and became a lieutenant colonel.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had a-- stayed in the-- in the Army for a long time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went to Vietnam.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He went to a lot of other places, partly because of his linguistic skills.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were-- they were a great variety of people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some of them came from Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of them came from Austria.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of them-- a large number of them came from Great Britain, because the number of the refugees who spoke both languages-- both German and English-- had fled into Great Britain, and we recruited them there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The colonel-- or then Lieutenant Eberhaal, flew to-- to London and actually did a lot of recruiting there with the help of OSS and so on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a great variety.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were some Dutch people who became interpreters.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
